## Summary: Web Interface Architecture for Claude Code Transcripts

I've completed a thorough exploration of the web interface files in this codebase. Here's what I found:

### **1. Template Files Location**
All templates are located in: `/Volumes/Samsung-4TB-APFS/Projects/claude-code-transcripts/src/claude_code_transcripts/templates/`

**Template Files:**
- **base.html** - Base template with CSS and JS injection
- **page.html** - Template for paginated conversation pages
- **index.html** - Main index/timeline page with search functionality
- **project_index.html** - Index page for projects (batch HTML generation)
- **master_index.html** - Master index listing all projects
- **macros.html** - Jinja2 macros for rendering various content blocks
- **search.js** - JavaScript for full-text search across pages

### **2. Message Rendering Architecture**

**User vs Assistant Messages:**
- **User messages**: Rendered by `render_user_message_content()` function
  - CSS class: `message user`
  - Border: 4px left border with `--user-border` color (#1976d2 - blue)
  - Background: `--user-bg` (#e3f2fd - light blue)
  - Role label: "User" in blue

- **Assistant messages**: Rendered by `render_assistant_message()` function
  - CSS class: `message assistant`
  - Border: 4px left border with `--assistant-border` color (#9e9e9e - gray)
  - Background: `--assistant-bg` (#f5f5f5 - light gray)
  - Role label: "Assistant" in gray

- **Tool Result messages**: Special handling as "Tool reply"
  - CSS class: `message tool-reply`
  - Background: #fff8e1 (light yellow)
  - Border: 4px left border with #ff9800 (orange)
  - Role label: "Tool reply" in orange (#e65100)

**Message Structure (macros.html):**
The `message()` macro creates:
```
<div class="message {role_class}" id="msg-{timestamp}">
  <div class="message-header">
    <span class="role-label">{role_label}</span>
    <time data-timestamp="{timestamp}">{timestamp}</time>
  </div>
  <div class="message-content">
    {rendered_content}
  </div>
</div>
```

### **3. Content Block Rendering**

The `render_content_block()` function handles these types:
- **text**: Markdown rendered text
- **image**: Base64-encoded images embedded in data URLs
- **thinking**: Claude's thinking process (yellow background #fff8e1)
- **tool_use**: Tool invocations with various specialized renderers
- **tool_result**: Tool execution results with special handling for commits

**Specialized Tool Renderers:**
- `render_write_tool()` - File write operations with green gradient
- `render_edit_tool()` - File edits with old/new diff view (orange gradient)
- `render_bash_tool()` - Shell commands with description
- `render_todo_write()` - Task lists with status indicators (‚úì, ‚Üí, ‚óã)

### **4. CSS/JS Architecture**

**CSS Variable System** (defined in `CSS` variable):
- Color scheme: User messages (blue), Assistant (gray), Tools (purple), Errors (red)
- Responsive design with mobile breakpoints (max-width: 600px)
- Dark/light mode support via CSS variables
- Theme colors:
  - `--user-bg`: #e3f2fd, `--user-border`: #1976d2
  - `--assistant-bg`: #f5f5f5, `--assistant-border`: #9e9e9e
  - `--thinking-bg`: #fff8e1, `--thinking-border`: #ffc107
  - `--tool-bg`: #f3e5f5, `--tool-border`: #9c27b0
  - Code background: #263238, Code text: #aed581

**JavaScript Functionality** (in `JS` variable):
- Timestamp formatting (locale-aware, shows time if today, date+time otherwise)
- JSON syntax highlighting in colored spans
- Content truncation/expansion with "Show more/less" buttons
- Max-height: 200px for truncated content with gradient fade

**Search JavaScript** (search.js):
- Full-text search across all pages
- Batch loading of pages (3 at a time)
- Result highlighting with `<mark>` tags
- Modal dialog for search interface
- Gist support (gisthost.github.io and gistpreview.github.io)
- URL hash integration (#search=query)

### **5. Overall Structure**

**Generation Flow:**
1. Parse JSONL/JSON session file
2. Group messages into conversations (separated by user prompts)
3. Paginate conversations (5 prompts per page)
4. Generate per-page files with messages using `render_message()`
5. Generate index.html with timeline of prompts and commits
6. Apply consistent CSS and JS to all pages

**Message HTML Structure:**
Each page contains:
- Messages rendered via `render_message()` function
- Messages grouped by conversation
- Continuation messages wrapped in `<details>` elements
- Pagination controls at top and bottom

**File Organization:**
- `/templates/` - Jinja2 templates and static JS
- Main module `__init__.py` - Rendering functions and CSS/JS strings
- Static CSS/JS embedded directly in template variables (not separate files)

### **6. Key Functions for Message Rendering**

- `render_message()` - Main dispatcher for user/assistant messages
- `render_user_message_content()` - User message processor
- `render_assistant_message()` - Assistant message processor  
- `render_content_block()` - Generic content block renderer
- `_macros.message()` - HTML wrapper macro
- `generate_html()` - Main HTML generation orchestrator

All CSS and JavaScript are embedded in Python string variables (`CSS` and `JS`) and injected into templates via `{{ css|safe }}` and `{{ js|safe }}` directives.

  1165‚Üí            var anchor = parts.length > 1 ? '#' + parts[1] : '';
  1166‚Üí            link.setAttribute('href', '?' + gistId + '/' + filename + anchor);

  1168‚Üí    }

   843‚Üídef render_user_message_content(message_data):
   844‚Üí    content = message_data.get("content", "")
   845‚Üí    if isinstance(content, str):
   846‚Üí        if is_json_like(content):
   847‚Üí            return _macros.user_content(format_json(content))
   848‚Üí        return _macros.user_content(render_markdown_text(content))
   849‚Üí    elif isinstance(content, list):
   850‚Üí        return "".join(render_content_block(block) for block in content)
   851‚Üí    return f"<p>{html.escape(str(content))}</p>"

   853‚Üí
   854‚Üídef render_assistant_message(message_data):
   855‚Üí    content = message_data.get("content", [])
   856‚Üí    if not isinstance(content, list):
   857‚Üí        return f"<p>{html.escape(str(content))}</p>"
   858‚Üí    return "".join(render_content_block(block) for block in content)
   859‚Üí
   860‚Üí
   861‚Üídef make_msg_id(timestamp):
   862‚Üí    return f"msg-{timestamp.replace(':', '-').replace('.', '-')}"
   863‚Üí
   864‚Üí
   865‚Üídef analyze_conversation(messages):
   866‚Üí    """Analyze messages in a conversation to extract stats and long texts."""
   867‚Üí    tool_counts = {}  # tool_name -> count
   868‚Üí    long_texts = []
   869‚Üí    commits = []  # list of (hash, message, timestamp)
   870‚Üí
   871‚Üí    for log_type, message_json, timestamp in messages:
   872‚Üí        if not message_json:
   873‚Üí            continue
   874‚Üí        try:
   875‚Üí            message_data = json.loads(message_json)
   876‚Üí        except json.JSONDecodeError:
   877‚Üí            continue
   878‚Üí
   879‚Üí        content = message_data.get("content", [])
   880‚Üí        if not isinstance(content, list):
   881‚Üí            continue
   882‚Üí
   883‚Üí        for block in content:
   884‚Üí            if not isinstance(block, dict):
   885‚Üí                continue
   886‚Üí            block_type = block.get("type", "")
   887‚Üí
   888‚Üí            if block_type == "tool_use":
   889‚Üí                tool_name = block.get("name", "Unknown")
   890‚Üí                tool_counts[tool_name] = tool_counts.get(tool_name, 0) + 1
   891‚Üí            elif block_type == "tool_result":
   892‚Üí                # Check for git commit output
   893‚Üí                result_content = block.get("content", "")
   894‚Üí                if isinstance(result_content, str):
   895‚Üí                    for match in COMMIT_PATTERN.finditer(result_content):
   896‚Üí                        commits.append((match.group(1), match.group(2), timestamp))
   897‚Üí            elif block_type == "text":
   898‚Üí                text = block.get("text", "")
   899‚Üí                if len(text) >= LONG_TEXT_THRESHOLD:
   900‚Üí                    long_texts.append(text)
   901‚Üí
   902‚Üí    return {
   903‚Üí        "tool_counts": tool_counts,
   904‚Üí        "long_texts": long_texts,
   905‚Üí        "commits": commits,
   906‚Üí    }
   907‚Üí
   908‚Üí
   909‚Üídef format_tool_stats(tool_counts):
   910‚Üí    """Format tool counts into a concise summary string."""
   911‚Üí    if not tool_counts:
   912‚Üí        return ""
   913‚Üí
   914‚Üí    # Abbreviate common tool names
   915‚Üí    abbrev = {
   916‚Üí        "Bash": "bash",
   917‚Üí        "Read": "read",
   918‚Üí        "Write": "write",
   919‚Üí        "Edit": "edit",
   920‚Üí        "Glob": "glob",
   921‚Üí        "Grep": "grep",
   922‚Üí        "Task": "task",
   923‚Üí        "TodoWrite": "todo",
   924‚Üí        "WebFetch": "fetch",
   925‚Üí        "WebSearch": "search",
   926‚Üí    }
   927‚Üí
   928‚Üí    parts = []
   929‚Üí    for name, count in sorted(tool_counts.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1]):
   930‚Üí        short_name = abbrev.get(name, name.lower())
   931‚Üí        parts.append(f"{count} {short_name}")
   932‚Üí
   933‚Üí    return " ¬∑ ".join(parts)
   934‚Üí
   935‚Üí
   936‚Üídef is_tool_result_message(message_data):
   937‚Üí    """Check if a message contains only tool_result blocks."""
   938‚Üí    content = message_data.get("content", [])
   939‚Üí    if not isinstance(content, list):
   940‚Üí        return False
   941‚Üí    if not content:
   942‚Üí        return False
   943‚Üí    return all(
   944‚Üí        isinstance(block, dict) and block.get("type") == "tool_result"
   945‚Üí        for block in content
   946‚Üí    )
   947‚Üí
   948‚Üí
   949‚Üídef render_message(log_type, message_json, timestamp):
   950‚Üí    if not message_json:
   951‚Üí        return ""
   952‚Üí    try:
   953‚Üí        message_data = json.loads(message_json)
   954‚Üí    except json.JSONDecodeError:
   955‚Üí        return ""
   956‚Üí    if log_type == "user":
   957‚Üí        content_html = render_user_message_content(message_data)
   958‚Üí        # Check if this is a tool result message
   959‚Üí        if is_tool_result_message(message_data):
   960‚Üí            role_class, role_label = "tool-reply", "Tool reply"
   961‚Üí        else:
   962‚Üí            role_class, role_label = "user", "User"
   963‚Üí    elif log_type == "assistant":
   964‚Üí        content_html = render_assistant_message(message_data)
   965‚Üí        role_class, role_label = "assistant", "Assistant"
   966‚Üí    else:
   967‚Üí        return ""
   968‚Üí    if not content_html.strip():
   969‚Üí        return ""
   970‚Üí    msg_id = make_msg_id(timestamp)
   971‚Üí    return _macros.message(role_class, role_label, msg_id, timestamp, content_html)
   972‚Üí

Usage: claude-code-transcripts all [OPTIONS]

  Convert all local Claude Code sessions to a browsable HTML archive.

  Creates a directory structure with: - Master index listing all projects -
  Per-project pages listing sessions - Individual session transcripts

Options:
  -s, --source PATH  Source directory containing Claude projects (default:
                     ~/.claude/projects).

                     archive).
  --include-agents   Include agent-* session files (excluded by default).
  --dry-run          Show what would be converted without creating files.
  --open             Open the generated archive in your default browser.

 javascript
 (function() {
     if (!document.querySelector('.message')) return;
     var fab = document.createElement('button');
     fab.className = 'filter-fab';
     fab.title = 'Show user messages only';
     fab.innerHTML = '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="white"><path d="M12 12c2.7 0 4.8-2.1 4.8-4.8S14.7 2.4 12 2.4 7.2 4.5 7.2 7.2 9.3 12 12 12zm0 2.4c-3.2 0-9.6 1.6-9.6 4.8v2.4h19.2v-2.4c0-3.2-6.4-4.8-9.6-4.8z"/></svg>';
     fab.addEventListener('click', function() {
         document.body.classList.toggle('user-only');
         fab.classList.toggle('active');
         fab.title = fab.classList.contains('active') ? 'Show all messages' : 'Show user messages only';
     });
     document.body.appendChild(fab);
 })();

Tool reply2026-02-26T01:18:43.109Z
Perfect! Now I have the complete picture. Let me compile my findings into a comprehensive report.

## Summary of Findings

I've investigated the generated HTML files and identified exactly why SVG icons and floating buttons aren't showing. Here's what I found:

### What's Actually There

1. **SVG markup IS present** - Not escaped or missing, it's actual valid SVG code
2. **CSS styling IS present** - Both `.user-icon` and `.filter-fab` classes are defined
3. **JavaScript IS present** - The FAB creation code exists and runs

### The Root Cause: Jinja2 Autoescape

The issue is in the **Jinja2 template rendering configuration**:

**File:** `/Volumes/Samsung-4TB-APFS/Projects/claude-code-transcripts/src/claude_code_transcripts/__init__.py` (lines 23-26)

```python
_jinja_env = Environment(
    loader=PackageLoader("claude_code_transcripts", "templates"),
    autoescape=True,  # <-- THIS IS THE PROBLEM
)
```

### How the Autoescape Breaks SVGs

**In the template** (`/Volumes/Samsung-4TB-APFS/Projects/claude-code-transcripts/src/claude_code_transcripts/templates/macros.html`, line 156):

```html
<span class="user-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="..."/></svg></span>
```

**In the generated HTML output**, the SVG gets HTML-entity-encoded because `autoescape=True`:

```html
<span class="user-icon">&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"&gt;&lt;path d="..."&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;</span>
```

When the browser renders this, it displays the encoded text as literal characters instead of rendering the SVG!

### Where Both SVGs Are Affected

1. **User message icons** - In `macros.html` line 156:
   ```html
   {% if role_class == 'user' %}<span class="user-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24">...</svg></span>{% endif %}
   ```

2. **Filter FAB button** - In `__init__.py` line 1156 (inside the JS string):
   ```javascript
   fab.innerHTML = '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="white"><path d="..."/></svg>';
   ```

The FAB actually works because it's set via `innerHTML` in JavaScript at runtime (which bypasses HTML encoding), but the user icons in the message headers remain encoded.

### CSS & JS Are Fine

- CSS is correctly injected via the `{{ css|safe }}` filter (line 7 of base.html)
- JS is correctly injected via the `{{ js|safe }}` filter (line 13 of base.html)
- The FAB JavaScript creates and appends the button correctly

### Summary of What You'll See in the HTML

**User icons in messages:**
- Present but HTML-encoded (`&lt;svg...&gt;` instead of `<svg...>`)
- CSS styles exist and would work if the SVG wasn't escaped
- Result: No icon appears, just empty space

**Filter FAB button:**
- SVG correctly rendered via JavaScript `innerHTML` (bypasses autoescape)
- CSS styling is present
- Result: Button appears and works correctly

The fix would be to either disable autoescape or use the `|safe` filter on SVG content in templates where inline SVG markup is intentional.

    94‚Üí    def test_handles_array_content_format(self, tmp_path):
    95‚Üí        """Test that user messages with array content format are recognized.
    96‚Üí
    97‚Üí        Claude Code v2.0.76+ uses array content format like:
    98‚Üí        {"type": "user", "message": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "..."}]}}
    99‚Üí        instead of the simpler string format:
   100‚Üí        {"type": "user", "message": {"content": "..."}}
   101‚Üí        """
   102‚Üí        jsonl_file = tmp_path / "session.jsonl"
   103‚Üí        jsonl_file.write_text(
   104‚Üí            '{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hello from array format"}]}}\n'
   105‚Üí            '{"type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hi there!"}]}}\n'
   106‚Üí        )
   107‚Üí
   108‚Üí        output_dir = tmp_path / "output"
   109‚Üí        output_dir.mkdir()
   110‚Üí
   111‚Üí        generate_html(jsonl_file, output_dir)
   112‚Üí
   113‚Üí        index_html = (output_dir / "index.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")
   114‚Üí        # Should have 1 prompt, not 0
   115‚Üí        assert "1 prompts" in index_html or "1 prompt" in index_html
   116‚Üí        assert "0 prompts" not in index_html
   117‚Üí        # The page file should exist
   118‚Üí        assert (output_dir / "page-001.html").exists()
   119‚Üí

class TestUserMessageUI:
    """Tests for user message right-alignment, icon, and filter button."""

    def test_user_messages_have_right_aligned_css(self, output_dir):
        """User messages should be styled to appear on the right side."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        page_html = (output_dir / "page-001.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # CSS should right-align user messages
        assert "message.user" in page_html
        assert "margin-left" in page_html

    def test_user_messages_have_icon_css(self, output_dir):
        """User messages should have a user icon via CSS."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        page_html = (output_dir / "page-001.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # CSS should add a user icon
        assert "user-icon" in page_html

    def test_floating_filter_button_css(self, output_dir):
        """A floating button should be styled for filtering user-only messages."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        page_html = (output_dir / "page-001.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # CSS should style the floating filter button
        assert "filter-fab" in page_html

    def test_floating_filter_button_js(self, output_dir):
        """JS should create and handle the floating filter button."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        page_html = (output_dir / "page-001.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # JS should create the filter button
        assert "filter-fab" in page_html
        # JS should toggle user-only mode
        assert "user-only" in page_html

    def test_user_only_mode_hides_non_user_messages(self, output_dir):
        """When user-only mode is active, non-user messages should be hidden."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        page_html = (output_dir / "page-001.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # CSS should hide non-user messages when body has user-only class

class TestUserMessageUI:
    """Tests for user message right-alignment, icon, and filter button."""

    def test_user_messages_have_right_aligned_css(self, output_dir):
        """User messages should be styled to appear on the right side."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        html = (output_dir / "index.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # CSS should right-align user messages
        assert "message.user" in html
        assert "margin-left" in html

    def test_user_messages_have_icon_css(self, output_dir):
        """User messages should have a user icon via CSS."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        html = (output_dir / "index.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # CSS should add a user icon
        assert "user-icon" in html

    def test_floating_filter_button_css(self, output_dir):
        """A floating button should be styled for filtering user-only messages."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        html = (output_dir / "index.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # CSS should style the floating filter button
        assert "filter-fab" in html

    def test_floating_filter_button_js(self, output_dir):
        """JS should create and handle the floating filter button."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        html = (output_dir / "index.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # JS should create the filter button
        assert "filter-fab" in html
        # JS should toggle user-only mode
        assert "user-only" in html

    def test_user_only_mode_hides_non_user_messages(self, output_dir):
        """When user-only mode is active, non-user messages should be hidden."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        html = (output_dir / "index.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # CSS should hide non-user messages when body has user-only class
        assert "user-only" in html
        assert "display: none" in html or "display:none" in html

    def test_truncatable_defaults_to_expanded(self, output_dir):
        """Truncatable content should be expanded by default, not collapsed."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        html = (output_dir / "index.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # JS should add 'expanded' class (not 'truncated') for tall content
        assert "wrapper.classList.add('expanded')" in html
        # JS should NOT default to truncated
        assert "wrapper.classList.add('truncated')" not in html

    def test_fab_no_message_guard(self, output_dir):
        """FAB should be created on all pages, not just pages with .message elements."""
        fixture_path = Path(__file__).parent / "sample_session.json"
        generate_html(fixture_path, output_dir)

        html = (output_dir / "index.html").read_text(encoding="utf-8")

        # JS should NOT have a guard that skips FAB creation when no .message elements
        assert "if (!document.querySelector('.message')) return;" not in html

   102‚Üí    function highlightTextNodes(element, searchTerm) {
   103‚Üí        var walker = document.createTreeWalker(element, NodeFilter.SHOW_TEXT, null, false);
   104‚Üí        var nodesToReplace = [];
   105‚Üí
   106‚Üí        while (walker.nextNode()) {
   107‚Üí            var node = walker.currentNode;
   108‚Üí            if (node.nodeValue.toLowerCase().indexOf(searchTerm.toLowerCase()) !== -1) {
   109‚Üí                nodesToReplace.push(node);
   110‚Üí            }
   111‚Üí        }
   112‚Üí
   113‚Üí        nodesToReplace.forEach(function(node) {
   114‚Üí            var text = node.nodeValue;
   115‚Üí            var regex = new RegExp('(' + escapeRegex(searchTerm) + ')', 'gi');
   116‚Üí            var parts = text.split(regex);
   117‚Üí            if (parts.length > 1) {
   118‚Üí                var span = document.createElement('span');
   119‚Üí                parts.forEach(function(part) {
   120‚Üí                    if (part.toLowerCase() === searchTerm.toLowerCase()) {
   121‚Üí                        var mark = document.createElement('mark');
   122‚Üí                        mark.textContent = part;
   123‚Üí                        span.appendChild(mark);
   124‚Üí                    } else {
   125‚Üí                        span.appendChild(document.createTextNode(part));
   126‚Üí                    }
   127‚Üí                });
   128‚Üí                node.parentNode.replaceChild(span, node);
   129‚Üí            }
   130‚Üí        });
   131‚Üí    }

   178‚Üí    async function performSearch(query) {

   200‚Üí

   203‚Üí        for (var i = 1; i <= totalPages; i++) {

   205‚Üí        }

   210‚Üí        var batchSize = 3;
   211‚Üí        for (var i = 0; i < pagesToFetch.length; i += batchSize) {
   212‚Üí            var batch = pagesToFetch.slice(i, i + batchSize);
   213‚Üí
   214‚Üí            // Create promises that process results immediately when each fetch completes
   215‚Üí            var promises = batch.map(function(pageFile) {
   216‚Üí                return fetch(getPageFetchUrl(pageFile))
   217‚Üí                    .then(function(response) {

   224‚Üí                        resultsFound += count;
   225‚Üí                        pagesSearched++;

   227‚Üí                    })
   228‚Üí                    .catch(function() {
   229‚Üí                        pagesSearched++;

   231‚Üí                    });
   232‚Üí            });
   233‚Üí
   234‚Üí            // Wait for this batch to complete before starting the next
   235‚Üí            await Promise.all(promises);
   236‚Üí        }
   237‚Üí
   238‚Üí        searchStatus.textContent = 'Found ' + resultsFound + ' result(s) in ' + totalPages + ' pages';

        page_convs = conversations[start_idx:end_idx]
        messages_html = []
        for conv in page_convs:

            for log_type, message_json, timestamp in conv["messages"]:
                msg_html = render_message(log_type, message_json, timestamp)
                if msg_html:

    # Calculate overall stats and collect all commits for timeline
    total_tool_counts = {}
    total_messages = 0

        for commit_hash, commit_msg, commit_ts in stats["commits"]:

    # Build timeline items: prompts and commits merged by timestamp
    timeline_items = []

        prompt_num += 1

    # Calculate overall stats and collect all commits for timeline
    total_tool_counts = {}
    total_messages = 0
    all_commits = []  # (timestamp, hash, message, page_num, conv_index)
    for i, conv in enumerate(conversations):
        total_messages += len(conv["messages"])
        stats = analyze_conversation(conv["messages"])
        for tool, count in stats["tool_counts"].items():
            total_tool_counts[tool] = total_tool_counts.get(tool, 0) + count
        page_num = (i // PROMPTS_PER_PAGE) + 1
        for commit_hash, commit_msg, commit_ts in stats["commits"]:
            all_commits.append((commit_ts, commit_hash, commit_msg, page_num, i))
    total_tool_calls = sum(total_tool_counts.values())
    total_commits = len(all_commits)

    # Build timeline items: prompts and commits merged by timestamp
    timeline_items = []

    # Add prompts
    prompt_num = 0
    for i, conv in enumerate(conversations):
        if conv.get("is_continuation"):
            continue
        if conv["user_text"].startswith("Stop hook feedback:"):
            continue
        prompt_num += 1
        page_num = (i // PROMPTS_PER_PAGE) + 1
        msg_id = make_msg_id(conv["timestamp"])
        link = f"page-{page_num:03d}.html#{msg_id}"
        rendered_content = render_markdown_text(conv["user_text"])

        # Collect all messages including from subsequent continuation conversations
        # This ensures long_texts from continuations appear with the original prompt
        all_messages = list(conv["messages"])
        for j in range(i + 1, len(conversations)):
            if not conversations[j].get("is_continuation"):
                break
            all_messages.extend(conversations[j]["messages"])

        # Analyze conversation for stats (excluding commits from inline display now)
        stats = analyze_conversation(all_messages)
        tool_stats_str = format_tool_stats(stats["tool_counts"])

        long_texts_html = ""
        for lt in stats["long_texts"]:
            rendered_lt = render_markdown_text(lt)
            long_texts_html += _macros.index_long_text(rendered_lt)

        item_html = _macros.index_item(
            prompt_num, link, conv["timestamp"], rendered_content, stats_html

        timeline_items.append((conv["timestamp"], "prompt", item_html))

    # Add commits as separate timeline items

        timeline_items.append((commit_ts, "commit", item_html))

    # Sort by timestamp

document.querySelectorAll('.truncatable').forEach(function(wrapper) {
    const content = wrapper.querySelector('.truncatable-content');
    const btn = wrapper.querySelector('.expand-btn');
    if (content.scrollHeight > 250) {
        wrapper.classList.add('truncated');
        btn.addEventListener('click', function() {

The search feature was on the index.html template. Since we're now using the single.html template (which doesn't have search), these search tests will fail. I need to either:
1. Remove the search feature tests

   161‚Üídef find_local_sessions(folder, limit=10):
   162‚Üí    """Find recent JSONL session files in the given folder.
   163‚Üí
   164‚Üí    Returns a list of (Path, summary) tuples sorted by modification time.
   165‚Üí    Excludes agent files and warmup/empty sessions.
   166‚Üí    """
   167‚Üí    folder = Path(folder)
   168‚Üí    if not folder.exists():
   169‚Üí        return []
   170‚Üí
   171‚Üí    results = []
   172‚Üí    for f in folder.glob("**/*.jsonl"):
   173‚Üí        if f.name.startswith("agent-"):
   174‚Üí            continue
   175‚Üí        summary = get_session_summary(f)
   176‚Üí        # Skip boring/empty sessions
   177‚Üí        if summary.lower() == "warmup" or summary == "(no summary)":
   178‚Üí            continue
   179‚Üí        results.append((f, summary))
   180‚Üí
   181‚Üí    # Sort by modification time, most recent first
   182‚Üí    results.sort(key=lambda x: x[0].stat().st_mtime, reverse=True)
   183‚Üí    return results[:limit]

   451‚Üídef parse_session_file(filepath):
   452‚Üí    """Parse a session file and return normalized data.
   453‚Üí
   454‚Üí    Supports both JSON and JSONL formats.
   455‚Üí    Returns a dict with 'loglines' key containing the normalized entries.
   456‚Üí    """
   457‚Üí    filepath = Path(filepath)
   458‚Üí
   459‚Üí    if filepath.suffix == ".jsonl":
   460‚Üí        return _parse_jsonl_file(filepath)
   461‚Üí    else:
   462‚Üí        # Standard JSON format
   463‚Üí        with open(filepath, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
   464‚Üí            return json.load(f)
   465‚Üí
   466‚Üí
   467‚Üídef _parse_jsonl_file(filepath):
   468‚Üí    """Parse JSONL file and convert to standard format."""
   469‚Üí    loglines = []
   470‚Üí
   471‚Üí    with open(filepath, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
   472‚Üí        for line in f:
   473‚Üí            line = line.strip()
   474‚Üí            if not line:
   475‚Üí                continue
   476‚Üí            try:
   477‚Üí                obj = json.loads(line)
   478‚Üí                entry_type = obj.get("type")
   479‚Üí
   480‚Üí                # Skip non-message entries
   481‚Üí                if entry_type not in ("user", "assistant"):
   482‚Üí                    continue
   483‚Üí
   484‚Üí                # Convert to standard format
   485‚Üí                entry = {
   486‚Üí                    "type": entry_type,
   487‚Üí                    "timestamp": obj.get("timestamp", ""),
   488‚Üí                    "message": obj.get("message", {}),
   489‚Üí                }
   490‚Üí
   491‚Üí                # Preserve isCompactSummary if present
   492‚Üí                if obj.get("isCompactSummary"):
   493‚Üí                    entry["isCompactSummary"] = True
   494‚Üí
   495‚Üí                loglines.append(entry)
   496‚Üí            except json.JSONDecodeError:
   497‚Üí                continue
   498‚Üí
   499‚Üí    return {"loglines": loglines}
   500‚Üí
   501‚Üí

+
def generate_html(json_path, output_dir, github_repo=None):
    output_dir = Path(output_dir)
    output_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)

    # Load session file (supports both JSON and JSONL)
    data = parse_session_file(json_path)

    # Extract session title from first user message

User2026-02-26T01:45:26.539Z


align tool reply to right, what do you think?


Assistant2026-02-26T01:45:34.662Z


Thinking
The user is asking my opinion on aligning tool reply boxes to the right. Let me think about this from a UI perspective.


Currently:
- User messages: right-aligned (margin-left: 15%)
- Assistant messages: left-aligned (margin-right: 15%)
- Tool replies: centered (margin-left: 7.5%, margin-right: 7.5%)


Tool replies are responses to tool calls made by the assistant. They're essentially "responses back to the assistant" - like when the assistant calls a tool and gets a result. So semantically, tool replies are input/data coming back, somewhat like user-side content.


But actually, tool replies are part of the assistant's workflow - the assistant calls a tool, gets a result, and continues. So they're more closely associated with the assistant's turn.


I think aligning them to the left with the assistant messages makes more sense visually, since they're part of the same conversational flow. Right-aligning them would blur the line with user messages and create confusion about who's speaking.


Assistant2026-02-26T01:45:35.112Z


I'd keep them left-aligned like assistant messages rather than right. Tool replies are part of the assistant's workflow (assistant calls tool, gets result back), so visually they belong on the assistant's side. Putting them on the right would make them look like user input, which could be confusing.


Want me to align them left (matching assistant) instead?

(function() {
    var userMsgs = document.querySelectorAll('.message.user');
    if (userMsgs.length < 2) return;
    var nav = document.createElement('div');
    nav.className = 'progress-nav';
    var track = document.createElement('div');
    track.className = 'progress-track';
    var line = document.createElement('div');
    line.className = 'progress-line';
    var fill = document.createElement('div');
    fill.className = 'progress-line-fill';
    track.appendChild(line);
    track.appendChild(fill);
    var dots = [];
    var gap = Math.min(28, Math.max(10, Math.floor((window.innerHeight * 0.75) / userMsgs.length)));
    userMsgs.forEach(function(msg, i) {
        var wrap = document.createElement('div');
        wrap.className = 'progress-dot-wrap';
        wrap.style.height = gap + 'px';
        wrap.style.display = 'flex';
        wrap.style.alignItems = 'center';
        var dot = document.createElement('div');
        dot.className = 'progress-dot';
        var tip = document.createElement('div');
        tip.className = 'progress-tooltip';
        var text = msg.querySelector('.message-content');
        var preview = text ? text.textContent.trim().substring(0, 60) : 'Message ' + (i + 1);
        if (preview.length >= 60) preview = preview.substring(0, 57) + '...';
        tip.textContent = (i + 1) + '. ' + preview;
        dot.addEventListener('click', function() { msg.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' }); });
        wrap.appendChild(dot);
        wrap.appendChild(tip);
        track.appendChild(wrap);
        dots.push({ dot: dot, msg: msg });
    });
    nav.appendChild(track);
    document.body.appendChild(nav);
    function updateProgress() {
        var scrollTop = window.scrollY || document.documentElement.scrollTop;
        var winH = window.innerHeight;
        var activeIdx = -1;
        for (var i = dots.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            var rect = dots[i].msg.getBoundingClientRect();
            if (rect.top <= winH * 0.4) { activeIdx = i; break; }
        }
        dots.forEach(function(d, i) {
            d.dot.classList.toggle('passed', i <= activeIdx);
            d.dot.classList.toggle('active', i === activeIdx);
        });
        if (activeIdx >= 0 && dots.length > 1) {
            var pct = (activeIdx / (dots.length - 1)) * 100;
            fill.style.height = pct + '%';
        } else {
            fill.style.height = '0%';
        }
    }
    var ticking = false;
    window.addEventListener('scroll', function() {
        if (!ticking) { requestAnimationFrame(function() { updateProgress(); ticking = false; }); ticking = true; }
    });
    updateProgress();
})();
"""

# Redesign: Progress Sidebar with Text Navigation + Page Polish

## Context
The user wants to replace the current dot-only progress bar on the right with a proper text-based navigation sidebar (inspired by a Datadog blog article TOC). User messages should appear as labeled waypoints with clickable text that scrolls to the corresponding message. The page should also get a visual polish pass.

## Files to Modify
- `src/claude_code_transcripts/__init__.py` ‚Äî CSS string (~line 974) and JS string (~line 1134)

## Changes

### 1. Replace Progress Nav with Text Sidebar (CSS + JS)

**Remove** the current `.progress-nav` / `.progress-dot` / `.progress-line` CSS and JS.

**Add** a new right-side sidebar navigation:
- Fixed position, right side, vertically centered
- Each waypoint: a short vertical line segment (left border) + truncated user message text (max ~40 chars)
- Active/passed waypoints get the blue highlight color (`var(--user-border)`)
- Current waypoint text is bold + blue; passed ones get a subtle blue line; future ones are gray
- Clicking any waypoint smooth-scrolls to that user message
- Numbered labels: "1. Add floating button..." format
- Hover: full text in a tooltip (for long messages)
- Hidden on screens < 1100px (needs enough room for sidebar + content)
- Max-height 80vh, overflow auto for sessions with many prompts

### 2. Page Visual Polish (CSS)

- **Header area**: Add a subtle bottom border under the `<h1>` and stats line for visual separation
- **Stats line**: Use small pill/badge style for each stat (prompts, messages, tool calls, commits)
- **Message spacing**: Increase gap between messages slightly (20px instead of 16px)
- **Message cards**: Subtler shadows, slight hover lift effect
- **Code blocks**: Slightly more padding, softer border radius
- **FAB button**: Move up slightly to avoid overlap with mobile nav (bottom: 80px)
- **Body**: Add right padding (~220px on desktop) to prevent content from being hidden behind the sidebar

### 3. JS Changes

Replace the progress bar IIFE with a new sidebar builder:
- Query all `.message.user` elements
- Build sidebar HTML with numbered text labels (truncated to ~40 chars)
- Intersection Observer or scroll listener to track which user message is in view
- Toggle `.active` class on the corresponding sidebar item
- Click handler: `msg.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' })`

## Verification
1. `uv run pytest tests/test_generate_html.py --snapshot-update` ‚Äî all tests pass
2. `uv run claude-code-transcripts all -o ~/Projects/claude-sessions-html` ‚Äî regenerate
3. Open a session with many prompts in browser to verify sidebar nav works

## Approved Plan:
# Redesign: Progress Sidebar with Text Navigation + Page Polish

## Context
The user wants to replace the current dot-only progress bar on the right with a proper text-based navigation sidebar (inspired by a Datadog blog article TOC). User messages should appear as labeled waypoints with clickable text that scrolls to the corresponding message. The page should also get a visual polish pass.

## Files to Modify
- `src/claude_code_transcripts/__init__.py` ‚Äî CSS string (~line 974) and JS string (~line 1134)

## Changes

### 1. Replace Progress Nav with Text Sidebar (CSS + JS)

**Remove** the current `.progress-nav` / `.progress-dot` / `.progress-line` CSS and JS.

**Add** a new right-side sidebar navigation:
- Fixed position, right side, vertically centered
- Each waypoint: a short vertical line segment (left border) + truncated user message text (max ~40 chars)
- Active/passed waypoints get the blue highlight color (`var(--user-border)`)
- Current waypoint text is bold + blue; passed ones get a subtle blue line; future ones are gray
- Clicking any waypoint smooth-scrolls to that user message
- Numbered labels: "1. Add floating button..." format
- Hover: full text in a tooltip (for long messages)
- Hidden on screens < 1100px (needs enough room for sidebar + content)
- Max-height 80vh, overflow auto for sessions with many prompts

### 2. Page Visual Polish (CSS)

- **Header area**: Add a subtle bottom border under the `<h1>` and stats line for visual separation
- **Stats line**: Use small pill/badge style for each stat (prompts, messages, tool calls, commits)
- **Message spacing**: Increase gap between messages slightly (20px instead of 16px)
- **Message cards**: Subtler shadows, slight hover lift effect
- **Code blocks**: Slightly more padding, softer border radius
- **FAB button**: Move up slightly to avoid overlap with mobile nav (bottom: 80px)
- **Body**: Add right padding (~220px on desktop) to prevent content from being hidden behind the sidebar

### 3. JS Changes

Replace the progress bar IIFE with a new sidebar builder:
- Query all `.message.user` elements
- Build sidebar HTML with numbered text labels (truncated to ~40 chars)
- Intersection Observer or scroll listener to track which user message is in view
- Toggle `.active` class on the corresponding sidebar item
- Click handler: `msg.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' })`

## Verification
1. `uv run pytest tests/test_generate_html.py --snapshot-update` ‚Äî all tests pass
2. `uv run claude-code-transcripts all -o ~/Projects/claude-sessions-html` ‚Äî regenerate
3. Open a session with many prompts in browser to verify sidebar nav works

‚úèÔ∏è Edit __init__.py

‚àí
(function() {
    var userMsgs = document.querySelectorAll('.message.user');
    if (userMsgs.length < 2) return;
    var nav = document.createElement('div');
    nav.className = 'progress-nav';
    var track = document.createElement('div');
    track.className = 'progress-track';
    var line = document.createElement('div');
    line.className = 'progress-line';
    var fill = document.createElement('div');
    fill.className = 'progress-line-fill';
    track.appendChild(line);
    track.appendChild(fill);
    var dots = [];
    var gap = Math.min(28, Math.max(10, Math.floor((window.innerHeight * 0.75) / userMsgs.length)));
    userMsgs.forEach(function(msg, i) {
        var wrap = document.createElement('div');
        wrap.className = 'progress-dot-wrap';
        wrap.style.height = gap + 'px';
        wrap.style.display = 'flex';
        wrap.style.alignItems = 'center';
        var dot = document.createElement('div');
        dot.className = 'progress-dot';
        var tip = document.createElement('div');
        tip.className = 'progress-tooltip';
        var text = msg.querySelector('.message-content');
        var preview = text ? text.textContent.trim().substring(0, 60) : 'Message ' + (i + 1);
        if (preview.length >= 60) preview = preview.substring(0, 57) + '...';
        tip.textContent = (i + 1) + '. ' + preview;
        dot.addEventListener('click', function() { msg.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' }); });
        wrap.appendChild(dot);
        wrap.appendChild(tip);
        track.appendChild(wrap);
        dots.push({ dot: dot, msg: msg });
    });
    nav.appendChild(track);
    document.body.appendChild(nav);
    function updateProgress() {
        var scrollTop = window.scrollY || document.documentElement.scrollTop;
        var winH = window.innerHeight;
        var activeIdx = -1;
        for (var i = dots.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            var rect = dots[i].msg.getBoundingClientRect();
            if (rect.top <= winH * 0.4) { activeIdx = i; break; }
        }
        dots.forEach(function(d, i) {
            d.dot.classList.toggle('passed', i <= activeIdx);
            d.dot.classList.toggle('active', i === activeIdx);
        });
        if (activeIdx >= 0 && dots.length > 1) {
            var pct = (activeIdx / (dots.length - 1)) * 100;
            fill.style.height = pct + '%';
        } else {
            fill.style.height = '0%';
        }
    }
    var ticking = false;
    window.addEventListener('scroll', function() {

(function() {
    var userMsgs = document.querySelectorAll('.message.user');
    if (userMsgs.length < 2) return;
    var nav = document.createElement('nav');
    nav.className = 'sidebar-nav';
    var list = document.createElement('ul');
    list.className = 'sidebar-list';
    var items = [];
    userMsgs.forEach(function(msg, i) {
        var li = document.createElement('li');
        li.className = 'sidebar-item';
        var label = document.createElement('span');
        label.className = 'sidebar-label';
        var content = msg.querySelector('.message-content');
        var preview = content ? content.textContent.trim().substring(0, 45) : 'Message ' + (i + 1);
        if (preview.length >= 45) preview = preview.substring(0, 42) + '...';
        label.textContent = preview;
        li.title = content ? content.textContent.trim().substring(0, 120) : '';
        li.appendChild(label);
        li.addEventListener('click', function() { msg.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' }); });
        list.appendChild(li);
        items.push({ el: li, msg: msg });
    });
    nav.appendChild(list);
    document.body.appendChild(nav);
    function updateSidebar() {
        var winH = window.innerHeight;
        var activeIdx = -1;
        for (var i = items.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            var rect = items[i].msg.getBoundingClientRect();
            if (rect.top <= winH * 0.4) { activeIdx = i; break; }
        }
        items.forEach(function(item, i) {
            item.el.classList.toggle('passed', i < activeIdx);
            item.el.classList.toggle('active', i === activeIdx);
        });
        var activeEl = nav.querySelector('.sidebar-item.active');
        if (activeEl) { activeEl.scrollIntoView({ block: 'nearest', behavior: 'smooth' }); }
    }
    var ticking = false;
    window.addEventListener('scroll', function() {
        if (!ticking) { requestAnimationFrame(function() { updateSidebar(); ticking = false; }); ticking = true; }
    });
    updateSidebar();
})();

+
(function() {
    var userOnly = false;
    var fab = document.createElement('button');
    fab.className = 'filter-fab';
    fab.title = 'Show user messages only';
    fab.innerHTML = '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="white"><path d="M12 12c2.7 0 4.8-2.1 4.8-4.8S14.7 2.4 12 2.4 7.2 4.5 7.2 7.2 9.3 12 12 12zm0 2.4c-3.2 0-9.6 1.6-9.6 4.8v2.4h19.2v-2.4c0-3.2-6.4-4.8-9.6-4.8z"/></svg>';
    fab.addEventListener('click', function() {
        userOnly = !userOnly;
        document.body.classList.toggle('user-only', userOnly);
        fab.classList.toggle('active', userOnly);
        fab.title = userOnly ? 'Show all messages' : 'Show user messages only';
        if (!userOnly) {
            var hash = window.location.hash;
            if (hash) {
                var target = document.querySelector(hash);
                if (target) { setTimeout(function() { target.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' }); }, 50); }
            }
        }
    });
    document.body.appendChild(fab);
    var userMsgs = document.querySelectorAll('.message.user');
    if (userMsgs.length < 2) return;
    var nav = document.createElement('nav');
    nav.className = 'sidebar-nav';
    var list = document.createElement('ul');
    list.className = 'sidebar-list';
    var items = [];
    userMsgs.forEach(function(msg, i) {
        var li = document.createElement('li');
        li.className = 'sidebar-item';
        var label = document.createElement('span');
        label.className = 'sidebar-label';
        var content = msg.querySelector('.message-content');
        var preview = content ? content.textContent.trim().substring(0, 45) : 'Message ' + (i + 1);
        if (preview.length >= 45) preview = preview.substring(0, 42) + '...';
        label.textContent = preview;
        li.title = content ? content.textContent.trim().substring(0, 120) : '';
        li.appendChild(label);
        li.addEventListener('click', function() {
            if (msg.id) { history.replaceState(null, '', '#' + msg.id); }
            msg.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' });
            if (userOnly) { setActive(i); }
        });
        list.appendChild(li);
        items.push({ el: li, msg: msg });
    });
    nav.appendChild(list);
    document.body.appendChild(nav);
    function setActive(idx) {
        items.forEach(function(item, i) {
            item.el.classList.toggle('passed', i < idx);
            item.el.classList.toggle('active', i === idx);
        });
        var activeEl = nav.querySelector('.sidebar-item.active');
        if (activeEl) { activeEl.scrollIntoView({ block: 'nearest', behavior: 'smooth' }); }
    }
    function updateSidebar() {
        if (userOnly) return;
        var winH = window.innerHeight;
        var activeIdx = -1;
        for (var i = items.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            var rect = items[i].msg.getBoundingClientRect();
            if (rect.top <= winH * 0.4) { activeIdx = i; break; }
        }
        setActive(activeIdx);
    }
    var ticking = false;
    window.addEventListener('scroll', function() {
        if (!ticking) { requestAnimationFrame(function() { updateSidebar(); ticking = false; }); ticking = true; }
    });
    updateSidebar();
})();
